insights: You're taking a great step by considering a study group for Calculus; collaboration often brings new insights and understanding. Keep an open mind as you learn from your peers!

Exploring online resources and video tutorials can offer you a variety of explanations and methods that might resonate with you more than traditional classroom approaches. Khan Academy and PatrickJMT are great places to start.
Identifying the specific topics in Calculus that challenge you is a smart move. Once you know these, you can focus your study and practice on these areas, making your learning more efficient.

Remember, it's completely normal to find certain subjects more challenging. Celebrate your progress in English and use that confidence to tackle the difficulties in Calculus. You're capable of mastering both!
